  "doc_id": "14389",
  "text": "We previously used the MAA to identify 73 women in the PEPIMalawi trial who were recently infected at the time of study enrollment (pregnant women, near the time of delivery) [CITATION_1] . In analyses of other cohorts of adults with HIV-1 subtype C infection where the duration of HIV infection was known, this MAA had a positive predictive value of 93.9% for identifying recent infection [CITATION_2] . Clinical data (a higher rate of in utero HIV transmission) and demographic data (younger age) also supported the classification of these 73 women as recently infected at the time of study enrollment [CITATION_3] . Data from this report provides additional biological evidence supporting this classification.",
